<br>
Roleplay is a wonderful thing and I enjoy it very much.<br>
<br>
HOWEVER,<br>
<br>
Every game has rules and they must be followed.  Please dont use RP to break the rules.  There's really ZERO argument to be made here.<br>
<br>
The rules state training is a violation of the Play Nice Policy.<br>
<br>
If you train someone, even in character, it is against the rules.<br>
<br>
The &quot;authorities&quot; get involved.<br>
<br>
It's not a difficult thought process to carry out.  Stop using Roleplay as an excuse.  <br>
<br>
How is it roleplay to &quot;call the guards&quot; by punching them, or in some other way attacking them?   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
