<br>
Of course, I never do this myself (and I don't have to any more), as I know that my own reputation, so important for a knight, would be ruined.<br>
<br>
All I want to say is that if you choose to invade a town, be prepared to meet its strong resistance without crying for help of the almighty Jindrack.<br>
<br>
I met a very insolent gnome once and had to go all the way to Ak'Anon to teach him.  Before I did, however, I had to dispose of three waves of mechanical trash that he led to me.  In the end I thought it was an interesting adventure.<br>
<br>
An attack on a town is itself outrageous for those who live there, so don't be so offended when one of the natives suddenly loses it.  And, as this happens very often, be prepared for it. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=277315">Sir Cadien Nachtfalke</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of Resolution</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eveningshadow>EveningShadow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 452<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/14/03 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just a brief note for those who raid other folks homes .</span><hr size=1> It's a-ok to train! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :thumb --><img src=http://www.spacespider.net/emo/thumbsup.gif ALT=":thumb"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
