<br>
1.  Do not train.  There is no excuse for this.  As far as I'm concerned, you train, you get petitioned and I WILL make sure a GM gets to you.<br>
<br>
2.  Do not taunt if you are unprepared to duel.  Fortunately, I rarely have this happen to me at least, but it does.<br>
<br>
3.  Do not go there expecting to wave around your penis and show how you pwn n00bs or whatever.  There is always a bigger fish.  Always.<br>
<br>
4.  Don't get upset if someone with more experience challenges you for no reason (note, I said no reason).  There are many reasons to turn down a duel.  If a level 60 challenges a level 20 to a duel, then you have every right to turn that duel down if they haven't even spoken to you.  Chances are, a level 60 allied fighter will get really POed if they start challenging youngins and will usually ICly step up to kick their arses.<br>
<br>
5.  Never mix up IC and OOC in a city seige environment.  Remember.  Those buildings you are attacking or defending are just pixels.  That is no excuse to screw yourself up over unless the players who are seiging (or defending) are doing it deliberately.  Do not ruin someone's fun for the sake of this pixels.  Instead, make it more fun.  Also see rule 1.<br>
<br>
6.  Don't be a sore loser.  You WILL lose some duels.  Just accept it, ask em how they beat you, laugh, chat some, and move on.<br>
<br>
7.  Don't be a cock waving winner.  Don't taunt people OOCly if you beat em.  Fine and dandy doing it IC if it's IC for your character, but always toss them a bone OOCly.  Most duels are a lot closer than most characters would like to think.  You, the player, know that.  Congratulate them on it.<br>
<br>
8.  Don't kill merchants unless you have to.  Ever.  Guards are enough.  Bankers are completely out.  If you kill merchants and so on, you have not warned several hours in advance and it is not a full RP event, then YOU ARE IMPEDING THE FUNCTION OF THAT CITY.  You are screwing up other people's playtime, and that is wrong.  A city seige, however, planned in advance (such as the Ak'anon seige) has given people enough notice.  It is their perogative to find the server message board and keep updated.<br>
<br>
9.  Don't complain about how a duel went, or exp loss, or whatever.  If you hit /d, you accept EVERYTHING that player is going to do to you, be it exp loss by DoTs or whatever.  If someone is intentionally, without a doubt, trying to cause you exp loss, then you can usually tell and that is fucked up, but if you duel a DoT class and then lose to them by DoT, don't complain.<br>
<br>
10.  Arenas are your friend.  Mass group PvP &gt;&gt; duels.  Use it when you can <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Baka's final thought:  ROLEPLAY.  If I raid a city, I want roleplay.  Duels are just on the side and part of the fun.<br>
<br>
Just my two pence <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p>Sir <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=190029" target="top">Bakanome Gwendyll</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
